      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im studying for my con law exam and kinda stuck on judicial philosophy. can u explain what originalism is and what some of the main arguments for it are?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that holds that judges should interpret the Constitution based on its original meaning, as understood by the Founding Fathers at the time of its adoption. Proponents argue that this approach ensures the Constitution's text and intent are preserved, preventing judges from imposing their own personal values or modern interpretations. They also claim that originalism is a more reliable method for resolving constitutional disputes, as it relies on historical evidence rather than subjective judicial discretion.",
